public class UniqueDataFieldValidator<T>
extends org.apache.wicket.validation.validator.AbstractValidator<T>

A validator for confirming field uniqueness for objects in the datastore. For example:

new TextField("username").add(new UniqeDataFieldValidator(User.class, "username"))

will ensure that the username chosen in the text field is not already in use by another User. If you are editing an existing user, you must indicate that user using the alternate constructor UniqueDataFieldValidator(IModel, String). Otherwise, the validator will fail because the value is in use by that user and will therefore not be unique if created again.

limitScope

public UniqueDataFieldValidator<T> limitScope(String field,
                                              org.apache.wicket.model.IModel<? extends Serializable> value)
Limit the scope of this validation. Allows you to ensure that a data field is unique only within a certain group. For example, 
 Site x = ...;
 validator.limitScope('site', siteModel);
would limit the unique field validation to a given site, allowing you to have objects with non-unique fields in different sites.

Parameters:
field - the name of the field in the object
value - the object that this field must represent
Returns:
this object, for chaining
